  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db6\u0da9 \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dba\u0dda \u0d9c\u0db8\u0db1 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Coastal rail travel at risk",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Railway Department has revealed that 76 tracks on the Moratuwa-Panadura-Wadduwa coastal railway line from Colombo to Matara are dilapidated.",
        "As a result, speed limits have been imposed on the same line and the dollar problem has affected repairs to the dilapidated track, railway sources said.",
        "We inquired about this from the Chief Engineer (Roads and Industries) of the Railway Department, HMKW Bandara, who said that due to the derailment of a considerable number of tracks in the region from Colombo to Wadduwa, the speed limit is 20 to 30 km per hour. That restrictions have been imposed.",
        "Accordingly, the dilapidated condition of the Colombo-Matara dual carriageway, which is considered to be the upper line of the Colombo-Payagala dual carriageway, will be seen at 31 points and the lower road from the Matara to Colombo will be dilapidated at 25 points, he said.",
        "He also said that the railway line from Payagala to Matara as a single track was in a dilapidated condition at ten places.",
        "He said that the main reason for the decay was the proximity of the coastal railway line to the sea."
      ],
